The paper proposes a probabilistic prediction approach for autonomous vehicles to accurately predict the behavior of surrounding vehicles and plan accordingly. This involves learning from real human demonstrations using hierarchical inverse reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as mixture models and deep neural networks, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with autonomous vehicles, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
